{
  "stem": "25639.8",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I somehow always felt that I must let her know that I am still here, I'm still struggling, and that if I only know that she is alive still, I will continue my struggle.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, if I had learned anything negative about my mother, I-- I would have given up, just like Anne Frank.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I would have probably given up like she, in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She gave off when her sister contracted typhus, and she was all alone.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She, too, was in Auschwitz, and she was shipped to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "By the way, in research I found that she was about six months older than I was at the time, when we were in Auschwitz, and that she went to Bergen-Belsen in October or November-- anyway, a few weeks before I did.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And-- but when her sister, Margot, died, she could no longer-- she could no longer go on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And-- and she probably caught it herself, but this I'm not sure of.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But it was very easy to give up and catch many things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I sometimes wonder how come that I made it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In these train rides, I'd be sitting on top of dead people who died of typhus, tuberculosis, or other serious ailments, and I came out without even-- without any scars in this area.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "What I have, however-- the long-term effect of the camp, is perhaps the way I should put it, was that I suffered from malnutrition and consequently, my shoulders did not grow properly.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And years later, first with the left arm, I couldn't even raise my arm to comb my hair, and so-- and then my right arm.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it had-- this had to be corrected through surgery.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Tests showed that the head of the humerus was rubbing against the acromion process.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
